# Solomon Henderson

**Type:** Person  
**Date Created:** 2025-01-26  
**Last Updated:** 2025-01-26  

## Overview

**Solomon Henderson** was a 17-year-old student involved in the tragic **Antioch High School Shooting** in **Nashville, Tennessee**, on **January 22, 2025**. Henderson opened fire in the school cafeteria, killing 16-year-old **Josselin Corea Escalante**, injuring another student, and ultimately taking his own life. The incident raised concerns about gun violence, mental health, and the influence of extremist ideologies among youth.

---

## Key Details

- **Full Name:** Solomon Henderson  
- **Age:** 17  
- **Incident Date:** January 22, 2025  
- **Location:** Antioch High School, Nashville, Tennessee  
- **Weapon Used:** 9mm Taurus G2C semi-automatic pistol  
- **Outcome:** Suicide following the attack  
- **Known Associations:** Under investigation; reports suggest possible ties to incel-related online communities. [[Africana Studies - Antioch High School Shooting, Antioch, TN]]

---

## Background and Motive

Authorities are still investigating Henderson’s background to understand the motive behind the shooting. Preliminary reports indicate:

- Henderson may have harbored **self-loathing** and feelings of social alienation. [New York Post](https://nypost.com/2025/01/23/nashville-school-gunman-17-who-killed-teen-girl-appeared-to-be-self-loathing-incel-adl-says/)
- Investigators are reviewing his **social media activity**, which suggests possible exposure to **incel-related ideologies** and extremist content. [NewsChannel5](https://www.newschannel5.com/news/purported-writings-from-antioch-high-school-shooter-show-his-plans)
- Friends and classmates described him as a **quiet individual** who exhibited signs of social withdrawal in the months leading up to the incident. [Metro Nashville Police](https://www.nashville.gov/news/2025/01/23/antioch-high-school-shooting-investigative-update)

---

## Timeline of Events

- **Morning of January 22, 2025:** Henderson was seen entering the school cafeteria carrying a backpack, which contained the firearm.  
- **11:09 AM:** He opened fire, discharging ten rounds within 17 seconds. [NewsChannel5](https://www.newschannel5.com/news/purported-writings-from-antioch-high-school-shooter-show-his-plans)  
- **Aftermath:** Henderson took his own life as law enforcement arrived.  

---

## Community Response

- **Counseling Services:** The school and local organizations provided counseling and trauma support to students and families affected by the tragedy.  
- **Gun Control Advocacy:** The incident reignited conversations about firearm regulations and school safety measures.  
- **Memorials:** A candlelight vigil was held to honor the victims and provide support to the grieving community. [Nashville.gov](https://www.nashville.gov/news/2025/01/24/supporting-nashvillians-impacted-by-antioch-high-school-shooting)

